  <h1>
   camera_set_view_angle
  </h1>
  You can use this function to update the angle of the view camera within the room. You give the unique camera ID value (as returned by the different
  <a href="camera_create.htm">
   <span>
    camera_create()
   </span>
  </a>
  functions) and then give the angle that you
    wish to set the camera view to. The default value is 0° with positive values rotating the camera
  <b>
   counter-clockwise
  </b>
  , ie: setting the value to 90 will rotate the camera 90° to the left.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">camera_set_view_angle(camera_id, angle)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      camera_id
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Cameras_And_Display/Cameras_And_Viewports/camera_create.htm">
        Camera ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The unique camera ID value returned when you created the camera
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      angle
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The new angle to set the camera view to
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">camera_set_view_angle(view_camera[0], point_direction(x, y, mouse_x, mouse_y));
</code></pre>
  The above code will set the view camera angle for the camera assigned to view port[0].
 </body>
